40|$|There {{are three}} options {{available}} for terminally ill insureds {{who are interested}} in accessing {{all or part of the}} face value of their life insurance policies: through the life insurance company (accelerated <b>death</b> <b>benefits),</b> through a viatical company (a via tical settlement), or through a via tical loan company (a via tical loan). This paper explores the definitions and tax regulations, calculations, and the claims process associated with accelerated <b>death</b> <b>benefits</b> and via tical settlements and loans...|$|R
